From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0009/N] flags-cflags.m4: re-derive CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM for BUILD pass

OpenJDK's `FLAGS_SETUP_CFLAGS_HELPER` sets `CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM` exactly
once, based on `OPENJDK_TARGET_OS`. That same global is then consumed
by `FLAGS_SETUP_CFLAGS_CPU_DEP` twice — once for the TARGET CPU pass,
once for the BUILD CPU pass.

When TARGET=bsd and BUILD=linux (our cross-compile), the BUILD JVM
gets `-DBSD` instead of `-DLINUX`. `share/runtime/semaphore.hpp` then
selects the BSD branch and tries to include `semaphore_bsd.hpp` for
the host-x86 buildjdk, which doesn't have `os/bsd/` on its include
path:

  fatal error: 'semaphore_bsd.hpp' file not found

The TARGET dispatch values have already been consumed by the time the
BUILD pass starts, so we can safely overwrite `CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM`
here from `OPENJDK_BUILD_OS`. The branches mirror those in
`FLAGS_SETUP_CFLAGS_HELPER`.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0009)

--- a/make/autoconf/flags-cflags.m4
+++ b/make/autoconf/flags-cflags.m4
@@ -405,6 +405,24 @@ AC_DEFUN([FLAGS_SETUP_CFLAGS],
   FLAGS_CPU_LEGACY=$OPENJDK_BUILD_CPU_LEGACY
   FLAGS_CPU_LEGACY_LIB=$OPENJDK_BUILD_CPU_LEGACY_LIB

+  # stopless-java-gc: CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM was set once in FLAGS_SETUP_CFLAGS_HELPER
+  # based on OPENJDK_TARGET_OS, but BUILD compiles need defines matching
+  # OPENJDK_BUILD_OS (otherwise e.g. cross-compiling linux-host -> bsd-target
+  # bleeds -DBSD into the buildjdk JVM, breaking semaphore.hpp dispatch).
+  # Re-derive here for the BUILD pass; the TARGET value has already been
+  # consumed at this point.
+  if test "x$OPENJDK_BUILD_OS" = xlinux; then
+    CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM="-DLINUX -D_FILE_OFFSET_BITS=64"
+  elif test "x$OPENJDK_BUILD_OS" = xmacosx; then
+    CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM="-D_ALLBSD_SOURCE -D_DARWIN_C_SOURCE -D_XOPEN_SOURCE"
+  elif test "x$OPENJDK_BUILD_OS" = xaix; then
+    CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM="-DAIX"
+  elif test "x$OPENJDK_BUILD_OS" = xbsd; then
+    CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM="-DBSD -D_ALLBSD_SOURCE -D_GNU_SOURCE -D_FILE_OFFSET_BITS=64"
+  elif test "x$OPENJDK_BUILD_OS" = xwindows; then
+    CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM="-D_WINDOWS -DWIN32 -D_JNI_IMPLEMENTATION_"
+  fi
+
   FLAGS_SETUP_CFLAGS_CPU_DEP([BUILD], [OPENJDK_BUILD_], [BUILD_])

   CC="$CC_OLD"
